value.0: A Zabrak improvement on the combat suit, this armor is good protection where speed and unrestricted movement are more important than bulky plating.

There are a variety of different kinds of armor intended to defend against the harsh enviroments of space, deflect the impact of blaster bolts and protect versus all types of damage that can be found on a battlefield. These suits are usually built in with a personal shield generator.

The BlasTech DL-22 Blaster Pistol is designed as a response to the MerrSonn DD6 weapon. The gun's barrel used a higher-grade focusing crystal to increase the damage dealt by the weapon's blasts, at the expense of the gun's stun setting. The DL-22 is held in high regard by those who prefer to customize their weapons.

A blaster is a ranged weapon that fires bursts of particle beam energy called blaster bolts from a replaceable power cell. The most commonly used weapon in the Galaxy, blasters' intense beams consisting of compacted high-energy particles and intense light can kill or paralyze their target, depending on their setting.

A double of curved panels forms an air-tight door. The transparent panes are of utmost curious material, neither liquid nor solid, but as strong and resistant than any treated iron and steel known to man.

Barab Ore is a resource to Barab I. It actually lays on the planet's surface, meaning it is exposed to high doses of radiation and torrential downpours daily. This ore can be found in concentrated ingots that actually stores and magnifies the radiation. When placed in a lightsaber, the ingots produces a blade that burns almost to the point of losing its cohesion.

Relacite is the second most common form of Adegan Crystals, this crystal doesn't focus energy as well as its rarer cousins, and thus usually reserved for use in training sabers. Adegan crystals are commonly used by Jedi as a main component of a lightsaber. Also known as "Ilum crystals," these rare Force-reactive stones are primarily found in the Adega system, and on the planet Ilum, but are also known to be found on the planet Halm.

The Durindfire gem is a precious crystal found on the planet Tatooine. The gem is key in adding a distinctive silver sheen to any lightsaber blade. This stone is traditionally used by the Jedi of the Halcyon/Horn family.

Few Durindfires ever leave the planet, though some are bought and sold by the Galactic Empire to help finance the Death Star project. The Alliance to Restore the Republic is able to pinpoint the Empire's various development sites by tracking the movement of these gems, and additionally used this information to uncover the origins of the TIE Phantom Project.

Hurrikaine crystals are deep blue to violet lightsaber crystals from the planet Hurikane admired for their unparalleled beauty. When used in lightsabers, they create blades that are very good at penetrating defenses.
